{
  "texts": [
    "For example, if there are five students, the one-hot vector for the fifth student will be [0, 0, 0, 0, 1].",
    "With the input of the student index vector, the student network outputs the estimated student ability parameter θ 5 for the fifth student.",
    "A similar process is applied to estimate the item parameter using item network F β.",
    "Both networks consist of several linear layers with a hyperbolic tangent activation function.",
    "Finally, the estimated item response parameters θ j and β i are used to predict the probability of student j giving a correct response to question item i using the sigmoid function, as in Equation 1."
  ]
}